<TITLE>Sloan: The United Nations, from a dream to a quagmire</TITLE>


<TEXT>
Following World War II, there was an understandable desire among the nations of the world who had <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">fought</EVENT> one or more of the Axis powers to <EVENT eid="e2" class="I_ACTION">create</EVENT> a world organization to <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">help</EVENT> avoid future wars and <EVENT eid="e4" class="OCCURRENCE">contesting</EVENT> evil. The seed of the current United Nations was <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE">initiated</EVENT> during WWII as a united effort to <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">defeat</EVENT> the Axis powers. The initial effort was <EVENT eid="e7" class="OCCURRENCE">led</EVENT> by U.S. President Franklin Roosevelt,British Prime MinisterWinston Churchill and Joseph Stalin of the USSR  all allies at the time. The first use of the term "United Nations" was <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE">made</EVENT> in <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="1942-01">early January 1942</TIMEX3> when 26 nations <EVENT eid="e9" class="OCCURRENCE">signed</EVENT> the original <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">declaration</EVENT>. By <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="1945">early 1945</TIMEX3> it had been <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">signed</EVENT> by 25 more. On <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="1945-10-24">Oct. 24, 1945</TIMEX3> the U.N. was officially <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">formed</EVENT>. <EVENT eid="e13" class="OCCURRENCE">Flushed</EVENT> from the victory of the Allies over the Axis powers, the U.S. Senate and House <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE">voted</EVENT> unanimously in <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="2017-12">December of 1945</TIMEX3> to <EVENT eid="e15" class="I_ACTION">see</EVENT> the permanent U.N. headquarters located in New York City. A major gift of $8.5 million was <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE">given</EVENT> by John D. Rockfeller, Jr. toward land acquisition. In <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE" value="2017-01">January of 1951</TIMEX3>, the U.N. building was open for business, full of lofty ideals and noble goals. 
 
However, the foundation of the U.N. <EVENT eid="e17" class="ASPECTUAL">began</EVENT> with a serious fatal flaw as the original charter had to be <EVENT eid="e18" class="OCCURRENCE">ratified</EVENT> by the U.S., France, the United Kingdom, the Republic of China and the USSR. The USSR, an ally against Hitler, was <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">led</EVENT> by a tyrant as ruthless as Hitler, Joseph Stalin, who soon <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">showed</EVENT> his true colors by <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE">gaining</EVENT> control of the countries of eastern Europe, supposedly <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE">freed</EVENT> by Russian troops from Nazi control. Later, China would also internally <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE">fall</EVENT> to communism and its brutal dictator, Chairman Mao. Between the two tyrants, Stalin and Mao, millions and millions of their own people were <EVENT eid="e24" class="OCCURRENCE">murdered</EVENT> in order for them to maintain control. Both tyrants <EVENT eid="e25" class="OCCURRENCE">proved</EVENT> to largely <EVENT eid="e26" class="OCCURRENCE">undermine</EVENT> any real effectiveness of the U.N. during their lifetimes. 
 
Aside from the U.N.'s <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE">efforts</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e28" class="OCCURRENCE">fight</EVENT> against the <EVENT eid="e29" class="OCCURRENCE">invasion</EVENT> of South Korea by North Korea in <TIMEX3 tid="t6" type="DATE" value="1950">1950</TIMEX3>, primarily <EVENT eid="e30" class="OCCURRENCE">defended</EVENT> by U.S. forces and command, the U.N. has been <EVENT eid="e31" class="OCCURRENCE">sliding</EVENT> steadily downhill since, <EVENT eid="e32" class="OCCURRENCE">embroiled</EVENT> in multiple scandals and ineffectiveness. Because any one of the original five members of the Security Council (including the USSR and China) could <EVENT eid="e33" class="OCCURRENCE">veto</EVENT> and <EVENT eid="e34" class="OCCURRENCE">prevent</EVENT> any meaningful actions the Council might <EVENT eid="e35" class="OCCURRENCE">take</EVENT>, the U.N. was structurally <EVENT eid="e36" class="I_STATE">doomed</EVENT> to be an ineffective force for good fighting evil. Evil was always present and could <EVENT eid="e37" class="OCCURRENCE">veto</EVENT> any worthy endeavor. That evil still exists, as does their veto. 
 
The U.N. has <EVENT eid="e38" class="OCCURRENCE">grown</EVENT> to 193 member states/nations, many of which are dictatorships. It has <EVENT eid="e39" class="I_ACTION">become</EVENT> a <EVENT eid="e40" class="OCCURRENCE">hotbed</EVENT> for graft and corruption, largely unaccountable, and the U.S. taxpayers <EVENT eid="e41" class="OCCURRENCE">pick</EVENT> up close to 25 percent of the annual bill. There was <EVENT eid="e42" class="OCCURRENCE">proven</EVENT> to be a huge kickback scandal surrounding them, U.N.'s "Oil-for-Food" fiasco in Iraq, as well as the sickening U.N. sex scandals in the Congo <EVENT eid="e43" class="OCCURRENCE">uncovered</EVENT> in <TIMEX3 tid="t7" type="DATE" value="2017-02">February of 2004</TIMEX3>. 
 
While no world <EVENT eid="e44" class="OCCURRENCE">war</EVENT> has <EVENT eid="e45" class="OCCURRENCE">transpired</EVENT> since the <EVENT eid="e46" class="OCCURRENCE">founding</EVENT> of the U.N., there have been 250 armed conflicts since <TIMEX3 tid="t8" type="DATE" value="1945">1945</TIMEX3>  an average of four per <TIMEX3 tid="t9" type="DURATION" value="PXY">year</TIMEX3>. The organization's history has also <EVENT eid="e47" class="I_ACTION">proven</EVENT> to be largely anti-Israel. The U.S. has been the leading protector of Israel, the only democracy in the Middle East. However, the recent <EVENT eid="e48" class="OCCURRENCE">vote</EVENT> by the U.S. to <EVENT eid="e49" class="OCCURRENCE">abstain</EVENT> from (instead of veto) a U.N. Security Council measure negatively affecting Israel has <EVENT eid="e50" class="OCCURRENCE">stunned</EVENT> Democrats, Republicans and Israel. It was an unforgivable act of <EVENT eid="e51" class="OCCURRENCE">betraying</EVENT> our best ally in the Middle East. In <TIMEX3 tid="t10" type="DATE" value="2016-12">the last month</TIMEX3> of his presidency, and after the presidential election, President Obama and Secretary of State John Kerry <EVENT eid="e52" class="OCCURRENCE">showed</EVENT> their true feelings. 
 
The U.N has for decades been a feckless, corrupt <EVENT eid="e53" class="OCCURRENCE">organization</EVENT> with minimal accountability and integrity. We would be better off to <EVENT eid="e54" class="OCCURRENCE">exit</EVENT> the U.N. and <EVENT eid="e55" class="OCCURRENCE">create</EVENT> a new organization composed of democracies and member <EVENT eid="e56" class="OCCURRENCE">nations</EVENT> with a proven record of non-aggression and respect for basic human rights. The noble U.N. dream of <TIMEX3 tid="t11" type="DATE" value="1945">1945</TIMEX3> never <EVENT eid="e57" class="OCCURRENCE">materialized</EVENT> and has <EVENT eid="e58" class="OCCURRENCE">become</EVENT> a <TIMEX3 tid="t12" type="DATE" value="2017">2017</TIMEX3> geopolitical quagmire.
</TEXT>


